Hi,

reviews.comment: Bilal responded surprisingly very quickly every time I messaged him even though we were in different time zones, lol! As a newbie I had many questions and he answered them thoroughly. I told him what file types I needed and he put them together in a basic package for me. He well understood what I wanted in a design when I sent him a few samples and did adjustments as required. I will go for sure go to him again if I need something else designed in the future.

This is my 2nd order with Bilal. I wanted to take a fun picture of my two sons and turn it into a logo for a book series I wrote about them. I had someone else start on it, but they couldn't finish it. I sent the original picture and what the unfinished logo looked like to Bilal. I had wanted a minimalist logo with just 2 colors, but what he did with it was awesome! I will definitely be back again soon with a 3rd logo I need redone!

I enjoyed working with Bilal because he kept making changes until I was completely happy with the logo. I love my logo!  He was informative and easy to communicate with and he did a great job of guiding me through the process.  Super happy I chose him and glad I chose Fiverr. I really love how Fiverr gives you a "Receipt of Doing" --not just a receipt. They truly understand that every step it takes to create something is a HUGE step--worthy to celebrated with proof! On the solo journey of entrepreneurship, acknowledgement is fantastic. I will be back!

I like my designs! I had a pretty clear vision upfront about what I wanted and the first round of designs he delivered were cute but not what I asked for so that was a bit of a time waster although we quickly got back on track.
